<subSubSection id="C31F2DDDBF24FFDA7EDEF3CEFCADD03A" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BBA7E56BF24FFDA7EDEF3CEFCCCD171" blockId="19.[196,1401,3165,3474]" box="[197,791,3166,3191]" pageId="19" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="B971A244BF24FFDA7EDEF3CEFEBBD171" box="[197,352,3166,3191]" pageId="19" pageNumber="430">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF24FFDA7F74F3CEFD6CD171" authority="Gray, 1837" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[367,695,3166,3191]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Vulpes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">Vulpes griseus Gray, 1837</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B6D740BBF24FFDA7CDCF3CEFCCCD171" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3784256310" box="[711,791,3166,3191]" pageId="19" pageNumber="430">
<collectingCountry id="F3123EC6BF24FFDA7CDCF3CEFCC8D171" box="[711,787,3166,3191]" name="Chile" pageId="19" pageNumber="430">Chile</collectingCountry>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA7E56BF24FFDA7EDDF311FCADD03A" blockId="19.[196,1401,3165,3474]" pageId="19" pageNumber="430">
Formerly believed to include an island form, which since has been recognized as Darwin’s Fox. The Pampas Fox has recently been suggested to be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF24FFDA7B1AF338FAA3D1C3" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[1281,1400,3240,3269]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Vulpes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">P. griseus</taxonomicName>
on the basis of a craniometric and pelage-characters analysis, leading to the conclusion that P. gymnocercus and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF24FFDA7C1DF363FDA5D012" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[518,638,3315,3348]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Vulpes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">P. griseus</taxonomicName>
are clinal variations of one single species, namely 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF24FFDA7B2EF363FE70D03A" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1854" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Lycalopex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="19" pageNumber="430" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gymmnocercus">Lycalopex gymmnocercus</taxonomicName>
. Four subspecies are recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
